%
% Parameters: 
% OutputFile: o 'Output', required: 'Resulting output data object'
% InputFile: i 'Input base file', optional: 'if set, dimensions for the canvas will be obtained from this file'
% Integer: w 'Width', default: 100: 'width of the canvas'
% Integer: h 'Height', default: 100: 'height of the canvas'
%
% Example: o = kkaplaincanvas(i, {'o','';'i','';'w',100;'h',100})
%
% Khoros helpfile follows below:
%
%  PROGRAM
% kaplaincanvas - Create a plain canvas for annotations
%
%  DESCRIPTION
% This routine creates a plain canvas - a kobject with dimensions w,h specified by either the parameters [-w] and [-h] or copied from the file specified with the parameters [-i], and with d and t dimensions equal to 1 and e dimensions equal to 3. The object will be saved in the file passed by the [-o] parameter. The color of the object is passed by the [-color] parameter.
% A canvas object is just a kobject with a plain background color that can be used for annotations.
%
%  
%
%  EXAMPLES
% All examples for the Annotate toolbox are listed on the $ANNOTATE/manual/index.html on-line manual.
